    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Frans van Cranevelt (Brussels, 16 September
                    1536)</head>
                <floatingText>
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">He was uncertain if he should reply to Frans van
                            Cranevelt’s pleasing poem in verse or prose. He should not be the only
                            one who is silent about losing Erasmus of Rotterdam, so he has poured
                            out his feelings in a poem; it will be van Cranavelt’s task to polish
                            it. 2. The Emperor occupied Arles after they killed every armed fighter
                            who resisted. The exiles from Florence attacked Genoa, but they were
                            repelled. They are hoping that the Emperor will bring peace to Italy.
                            The rest of the news briefly: Péronne is under siege; Damme has
                            capitulated to the Emperor; the fleet has set sail for the British
                            ocean; Cornelis de Schepper and Jean Godschalk went to Zeelandia the day
                            before yesterday; and the Persians are really squeezing the Turks.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/23388B64-82AD-4912-ABC0-C7C82C27F220
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.1"><app xml:id="app.1">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.1"/>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III" xml:id="rdg.1">Reverendissimi domini</rdg>
                    </app> Nicolai <app xml:id="app.2">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.2">Olai</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III" xml:id="rdg.2">Olahi</rdg>
                    </app> ad eundem responsio. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">[1.] Subdubius fui aliquandiu, Ornatissime Craneveldi, an soluta
                    oratione vel numeris, quorum iam a multis annis in desuetudinem <app
                        xml:id="app.3">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.3"><del corresp="Olahus">venit</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">veni</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III" xml:id="rdg.3">veni</rdg>
                    </app> ad tua carmina, ut meum <app xml:id="app.4">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.4"><del corresp="Olahus">esse potest</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">est</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III" xml:id="rdg.4">est</rdg>
                    </app> iudicium, non inconcinna responderem. Ne tamen solus viderer in tanti
                        <persName>amici</persName><note xml:id="note.1">Erasmus of Rotterdam.</note>
                    mei morte, mihi ob amicitiam nostram mutuam <app xml:id="app.5">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.5"><del corresp="Olahus">maxima</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">maxime</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III" xml:id="rdg.5">maxime</rdg>
                    </app> certe acerba tacere, et eius fatum non deflere, hos qualescumque numeros
                    inter meas urgentes et molestas aulicas occupationes effudi potius, <app
                        xml:id="app.6">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.6"><del corresp="Olahus">qua</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">quam</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III" xml:id="rdg.6">quam</rdg>
                    </app> scripsi, quos ad te mitto. Tuum erit eorum ineptias tollere et polire,
                    tandemque ad me remittere litura abunde ornatos. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">[2.] <persName>Caesar</persName><placeName>Arelato</placeName><note
                        xml:id="note.2">Arles.</note> potitus est interfectis, uti dicunt, omnibus
                    eius praesidionariis<note xml:id="note.3">‘which serves as a guard’, <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Hoven</hi> 2006, 430.</note> militibus et civibus.
                    Exsules Florentini, conscriptis in Italia pecunia Gallica militibus, aggressi
                    nuper fuere <placeName>Genuam</placeName> duabus ex partibus, sed repulsi magna
                    eorum caede. Spes est caesaris exercitum, qui ad Italiam in <app xml:id="app.7">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.7"><del corresp="Olahus">parte
                                servanda</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr">pace
                            servandam</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III" xml:id="rdg.7">pace servandam</rdg>
                    </app> relictus fuit, eos brevi prostraturum. <app xml:id="app.8">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.8"><del corresp="Olahus">Perona</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">Peronaeque</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III" xml:id="rdg.8"><del corresp="Olahus">Perona</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">Peronae</add></rdg>
                    </app><note xml:id="note.4">Péronne.</note> obsidio soluta est.<note
                        xml:id="note.5">The siege ended on 11 September, 1536.</note> Et non spero
                    aliquid nobis magnae laudis ex hac nostra expeditione venturum, militibus iam,
                    ut audio, domum redire cupientibus. <app xml:id="app.9">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.9"><del corresp="Olahus">Dani</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">Dammum</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III" xml:id="rdg.9">Dammum</rdg>
                    </app><note xml:id="note.6">Damme.</note> oppidum iampridem se <app
                        xml:id="app.10">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.10"><del corresp="Olahus">dedit</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">dedidit</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III" xml:id="rdg.10">dedidit</rdg>
                    </app> caesari. Nunc expedita fuit classis satis valida ad Oceanum Britannicum,
                    si quid boni nostri facere poterint. Praefecti <app xml:id="app.11">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.11"><del corresp="Olahus">his</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">huic</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III" xml:id="rdg.11">hinc</rdg>
                    </app> dominus de <app xml:id="app.12">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.12">Benuir</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III" xml:id="rdg.12"><del corresp="Olahus"> Benuir</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">Byren</add></rdg>
                    </app><note xml:id="note.7">We do not know him more closely.</note> et <app
                        xml:id="app.13">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.13"><del corresp="Olahus">Brodarod</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">Brodaroc</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III" xml:id="rdg.13"><del corresp="Olahus">Brodarod</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">Bredarod</add></rdg>
                    </app>.<note xml:id="note.8">We do not know him more closely.</note> Commissarii
                    dati Cornelius <app xml:id="app.14">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.14"><del corresp="Olahus"
                            >Scepperus</del></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III" xml:id="rdg.14"><add corresp="Olahus" type="insert"
                                >Scepperus</add></rdg>
                    </app> et <persName>Gothschalcus</persName><note xml:id="note.9">Jean
                        Godschalck.</note> nostri, qui nudiustertius in Zelandiam hinc solverunt.
                    Persae dicuntur <app xml:id="app.15">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.15"><del corresp="Olahus">Turcae</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">Turcis</add> nunc</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III" xml:id="rdg.15">nunc Thurcis</rdg>
                    </app> instare acerrime, cuius rei causa Turcarum caesar praesidionarios suos
                    milites ad se ex finibus Hungariae revocasse dicitur. Nunc tempus esset, si
                    principes <app xml:id="app.16">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.16"><del corresp="Olahus">Christinae</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">Christiani</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III" xml:id="rdg.16">Christiani</rdg>
                    </app> in recuperanda Hungaria Ferdinando regi nostro adessent. Alia nunc nulla
                    habeo. Bene vale. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.4"><placeName>Bruxellae</placeName> 16. Septembris 1536. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.5">[Elegia ad sepulchrum Erasmi Roterodami]<note xml:id="note.10"><hi
                            rend="smallcap">Hegedüs</hi> 1906, 424–426; <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Fógel–Juhász</hi> 1934, 34–36; <hi rend="smallcap">Neagu</hi> 2003,
                        346–348. In Romanian: <hi rend="smallcap">Capoianu–Costa–Nicolae</hi> 2022,
                        1234–1241.</note></p>
                <p xml:id="p.6"> [Epitaphium eiusdem per eundem]<note xml:id="note.11"><hi
                            rend="smallcap">Hegedüs</hi> 1906, 426; <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Fógel–Juhász</hi> 1934, 36; <hi rend="smallcap">Neagu</hi> 2003, 349.
                        In Romanian: <hi rend="smallcap">Capoianu–Costa–Nicolae</hi> 2022,
                        1240–1243.</note></p>
                <p xml:id="p.7">[Aliud eiusdem]<note xml:id="note.12"><hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Hegedüs</hi> 1906, 427; <hi rend="smallcap">Fógel–Juhász</hi> 1934,
                        36–37; <hi rend="smallcap">Neagu</hi> 2003, 349. In Romanian: <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Capoianu–Costa–Nicolae</hi> 2022, 1242–1243.</note></p>
                <p xml:id="p.8"> [Aliud eiusdem]<note xml:id="note.13"><hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Hegedüs</hi> 1906, 427; <hi rend="smallcap">Fógel–Juhász</hi> 1934, 37;
                            <hi rend="smallcap">Neagu</hi> 2003, 350. In Romanian: <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Capoianu–Costa–Nicolae</hi> 2022,
                    1242–1243.</note><?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?></p><?oxy_custom_end?>
            </div>
